      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While the UN's structural flaws are undeniable, declaring it a complete failure ignores its essential function in preventing global chaos. It remains the only universal forum where nations, even rivals, are forced to negotiate and adhere to a shared set of international norms. Reform efforts are absolutely necessary, focusing on limiting veto abuse, because abandoning the concept of international governance would lead to a far more dangerous world.",
      "source": "target",
